%
% === ORCHESTRAL NOCTURNE — "White Room" Scene ===
% Form: A(m1-8) B(m9-16) C(m17-24) D(m25-32) E(m33-40)
% Solo piano → +celesta → +strings/harp → +woodwinds → string core → piano return
% Harmonic palette: Db major / Bb minor, unresolved cadences, plagal motion
%
V:PianoRH clef=treble name="Piano"
%slot=lead %role=main_melody %register=upper_mid %dyn=pp %art=legato
%reason=Opens alone with childlike descending motif; establishes the nocturne's intimate voice. Hands off lead to winds/strings in D/E, returns for loop closure.
V:PianoLH clef=bass name="Piano"
%slot=bass %role=arpeggiated_harmony %register=mid_low %dyn=pp %art=legato
%reason=Gentle broken chords provide harmonic foundation; yields to harp in C section for orchestral color shift.
V:Celesta clef=treble name="Celesta"
%slot=color %role=bell_halo %register=high %dyn=pp %art=detached_legato
%reason=Sparse bell-like doublings add uncanny shimmer without competing; enters in B to signal the dream deepening.
V:Flute clef=treble name="Flute"
%slot=lead %role=echo_melody %register=upper_mid %dyn=p %art=legato
%reason=Echoes the piano's motif like a distant thought; takes lead in D while piano recedes.
V:Oboe clef=treble name="Oboe"
%slot=countermelody %role=hymn_answer %register=mid %dyn=pp %art=legato
%reason=Warm sustained counterline enriches without stealing focus; enters only in D for brief companionship.
V:Harp clef=treble name="Harp"
%slot=pad %role=arpeggiated_harmony %register=wide %dyn=pp %art=rolled
%reason=Takes over left-hand arpeggio role from piano; provides shimmering harmonic bed for string/wind bloom.
V:Vln1 clef=treble name="Violin I"
%slot=lead %role=emotional_melody %register=upper_mid %dyn=p %art=legato
%reason=Briefly becomes the emotional core in E section; the warmest voice in the piece before retreating.
V:Vln2 clef=treble name="Violin II"
%slot=harmony %role=inner_sustain %register=mid %dyn=pp %art=legato
%reason=Sustained thirds and sixths below melody; adds warmth without motion that would disturb the stillness.
V:Viola clef=alto name="Viola"
%slot=pad %role=mid_sustain %register=mid_low %dyn=pp %art=legato
%reason=Warm low-mid sustained tones create the muted string pad atmosphere; breathes slowly.
V:Cello clef=bass name="Cello"
%slot=bass %role=pedal_tone %register=low %dyn=pp %art=legato
%reason=Long pedal tones anchor the harmonic field; never moves fast, just holds the room steady.
%
